{"TopicId":123599,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Aerodynamic effects causing lag","CreatedByName":"bueskyd","CreatedById":150784,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-10-23T07:37:05Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"bueskyd","CreatedById":150784,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-10-23T07:37:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EKsp usually run very smoothly with 60 FPS, but as soon as aerodynamic effect start, the fps drops to 30 or less.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027m using KSP v. 1.0.4, and it\u0027s on steam.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI have the following parts in my PC:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ei5 6600k\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGTX 970\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E16 GB of ram running at 2133 MHZ\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESamsung SSD 850 EVO\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-10-23T09:53:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHi bueskyd, there is a slider for the aeroFX in the Settings screen and in the flight screen options when you press escape in flight.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bueskyd","CreatedById":150784,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-10-23T14:15:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI just tried disabling aeroFX completely, it still happens.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-10-25T20:03:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThere is a pretty severe memory leak with the reentry temperature gauges, if enabled. Press F10 before re-entry.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sal_vager\u0022 data-cite=\u0022sal_vager\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EThat was fixed already.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015